eus's text, rendering his poetry into spirited, contemporary prose and uncorking a forgotten classic that will appeal to drinkers of all kinds and (legal) ages.Arguing that moderation, not abstinence, is the key to lasting sobriety, and that drinking can be a virtue if it is done with rules and limits, Obsopoeus teaches us how to manage our drinking, how to win friends at social gatherings, and how to give a proper toast. But he also says that drinking to excess on occasion is okay-and he even tells us how to win drinking games, citing extensive personal experience.Complete with the original Latin on facing pages, this sparkling work is as intoxicating today as when it was first published.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aDrinking of alcoholic beveragesvEarly works to 1800. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aBacchus.  aBon Appetit.  aGerman wine.  aMark Forsyth.  aShort History of Drunkenness.  aWine Spectator.  aalcoholism.  aancient wine.  abinge drinking.  acollege drinking.  adrinking customs.  adrinking etiquette.  aexcessive drinking.  agifts for foodies.  agifts for groomsmen.  agifts for wine enthusiasts.  agifts for wine lovers.  agod of wine.  airresponsible drinking.  aresponsible drinking.  arules of toasting.  aself help.  ateaching responsible drinking.  avineyards.  aviniculture.  awine culture.  awine shops.1 aFontaine, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFontaine, Michael.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBoo